data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[,ru:di'mentri]
 Cách viết khác:
 rudimental
◘[,ru:di'məntl]
 ■như rudimental

Anh - Anh
rudimentary
[ˌru:dɪ'mɛnt(ə)ri]
■ adjective
1》 involving or limited to basic principles.
2》 relating to an immature, undeveloped, or basic form.
Derivatives
rudimentarilyadverb

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
rudimentary
▸ adjective
1rudimentary carpentry skills: BASIC, elementary, primary, fundamental, essential.
2the equipment was rudimentary: PRIMITIVE, crude, simple, unsophisticated, rough (and ready), makeshift.
3a rudimentary thumb: VESTIGIAL, undeveloped, incomplete; Biology abortive, primitive.
Opposites
advanced, sophisticated, developed.

Từ điển Kỹ thuật (EN)
■ thô sơ
